Buti Manamela says ANC men must be active in the fight against domestic violence and patriarchy. JOHANNESBURG - The social transformation commission has recommended that all men in the African National Congress (ANC) should hold marches against the violence of women and children.The commissions Lindiwe Sisulu and Buti Manamela on Wednesday raised concerns of crimes against women and children.Manamela says that ANC men must be active in the fight against domestic violence and patriarchy. ANC branches should all hold men s marches against violence of women and children under the banner of not in my name .Among other recommendations included physical education being made compulsory in schools and the distribution of free sanitary pads.